Considering plant habits, both tree and non-arboreous species were reduced in their future extent of occurrence compared to present times. However, reductions in high occurrence probability areas were most severe for non-arboreous species, compared to tree species, under both climate change scenarios (
 Fig 3A). This reduction was greater under the pessimistic scenario of climate change (H = 107.15, df = 5; P = 0.0001; 
 Fig 3A).
